@TwoStars: of course you realize that all of [Pawn of Ulamog](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pawn of Ulamog)'s tokens will die bafore you can use them for anything, right?


Anyway, it's cooler than coolness itself. Bringing any of you creatures with thoughness over 1 two turns earlier has a nearly-infinite combo potential. Zombies eat my brains if this doesn't get in some really broken standard deck.

Sadly, it doesn't really match Innistrad's zombies, given that its best zombie support until now comes from tokens ([Undead Alchemist](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Undead Alchemist), [Army of the Damned](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Army of the Damned), M12's [Call to the Grave](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Call to the Grave)) which don't get anything positive from this.
